Steps to install SASS:

1. Check if Node.js is installed:
   node --version

2. If Node.js is not installed, install Node Version Manager (nvm):
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

3. Restart terminal or source the nvm script:
   source ~/.bashrc

4. Install Node.js version 20.16:
   nvm install 20.16
   nvm use 20.16

5. Initialize npm project (if not already done):
   npm init -y

6. Install SASS:
   npm install sass

7. Verify SASS installation:
   npx sass --version
